  "body": "Buidler shouldn't allow sending incorrect JSON-RPC requests, as they lead to hard to debug errors.\r\n\r\nIt now allows using `undefiend` as `gas` param of `eth_call` and possibly other RPC methods.\r\n\r\nHow to reproduce it:\r\n\r\n1. Clone this repo at the exact commit that is linked: https://github.com/ajsantander/buidler-aragon-experiment/commit/c1979beafb4134a80b05f49fa087604f9032c9f6\r\n2. `npm i ganache@6.4.3`\r\n3. Run ganache in a separate terminal\r\n4. Run `npx buidler aragon:new_dao`\r\n\r\nThis will make Ganache crash because of an `eth_call` with `undefined` set as `gas`.\r\n\r\nThis behavior is handled in newer Ganache versions, so it doesn't crash anymore, but Buidler shouldn't allow it anyway.\r\n\r\nThere are, at least, two alternatives here:\r\n\r\n1. We throw an error if an `undefined` is used. This may be hard on our users, especially since this kind of requests are normally done after `await`s and the async context will probably be lost (i.e. incomplete js stack traces)\r\n2. We remove every undefined from the relevant calls.\r\n\r\nI'm more inclined for (2).\r\n\r\nThanks @ajsantander for reporting this :)",
